      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sound 1999 Porsche 911 Carrera, featuring the high-revving 3.4L M96 flat-six engine mated to a precise 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox. This 996.1 variant retains the desirable cable-actuated throttle for superior modulation. The chassis is dialed in with a refreshed multi-link rear suspension and upgraded Bilstein B6 dampers, providing excellent lateral stability and feedback. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with a ceramic dual-row solution, and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) was replaced concurrently. The cooling system has been overhauled with a low-temp thermostat and aluminum radiators to manage thermal loads during spirited driving. While the exterior shows minor stone chips and patina consistent with enthusiast use, the drivetrain remains tight with no bore scoring or AOS issues. A true driver's spec for those prioritizing longitudinal and lateral performance over concours perfection.",
